
[1]serpentine-stone

   SER'PENTINE-STONE, either shades and spots resembling a serpent's skin.
   Serpentine is often nearly allied to the harder varieties of steatite
   and potstone. It prisents two varieties, precious serpentine, and
   common serpentine.
